<br>
I have a good 1h slash weapon (Halcyon Broadsword) and a good 2h sword (Fiery Avenger), I'd have to say myself, that I tend to use the Fiery Avenger more.  I've noticed that on the Paladins of Norrath page, it seems many of the paladins would tend to use the Halcyon Broadsword, because of the added AC of a shield.  I can't argue this point.  I use Fiery Avenger because I like seeing big numbers, I can bash with it, from all the tests I've done, it seems to have a better damage output, but I sacrifice AC for it.  I do however, gain some useful stats with it as well.  I also use Fiery Avenger because I didn't get it on my own, but with the help of friends, so I also use it to honor them.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Anyway, it really tends to what item you are using I think.  Fiery Avenger allows bash, which REALLY helps out a lot.  Taunting a mob isn't hard at all as a paladin, throw a few stuns on it, and it'll beat on you all day long.  I tend to group with a 54 rogue a lot (Darkcana) and I don't have much trouble keeping him from getting hit, as long as I use stuns.  So honestly, it would probably be more efficient for me to use a 1h slash weapon, because I tend to tank more often.<br>
<br>
